Monaco midfielder Aurelien Tchouameni’s new club has been revealed. According to football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, Tchouameni has signed a five-year deal with Real Madrid that will see him remain at Santiago Bernabeu until 2027. Romano disclosed this in a tweet via his Twitter handle on Tuesday afternoon. He tweeted: “Aurelién Tchouameni to Real Madrid, here we go! Talks were at final stages yesterday night between Real and Monaco, it’s now fully agreed after final meeting for €80m plus add-ons to €100m.#RealMadrid “Tchouaméni only wanted Real with a contract until 2027 already agreed. “Paris Saint-Germain were ready to offer more than Real Madrid for Tchouaméni – they left the negotiations last weekend after player decision. “Liverpool also wanted him but the player was very clear: only Madrid.”